      <item>
        <title>Summer update</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;Two very interesting papers were published this month. The first is a Zika project with the &lt;a href=&quot;https://contnet2017.github.io/&quot;&gt;Contagion on Networks&lt;/a&gt; team showing that the asymmetric transmission across sexes leads to a double epidemic transitions; the paper was published in &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.pnas.org/content/early/2017/08/07/1703073114.full&quot;&gt;PNAS&lt;/a&gt;. The second one is the result of an SFI working group, which started by studying the strategies of algae life cycles and ended up re-discovering game theory by studying political dynamics on modular networks; this crazy paper was published in &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nature.com/articles/s41598-017-07621-x&quot;&gt;Scientific Reports&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
